00:07:48.460 --> 00:07:50.310
You wake up one morning in July.

00:07:50.310 --> 00:07:52.630
And I don't know
if any of you ever

00:07:52.630 --> 00:07:58.059
had the pleasure of
being in Alabama in July,

00:07:58.059 --> 00:07:59.600
but I'm fixing to
tell you something.

00:07:59.600 --> 00:08:01.460
This is true.

00:08:01.460 --> 00:08:03.460
You don't want to come
to Alabama in July.

00:08:03.460 --> 00:08:04.740
It's too hot.

00:08:04.740 --> 00:08:08.645
And so this hot day, I woke
up like any other morning,

00:08:08.645 --> 00:08:13.480
and about 12, 1 o'clock in
the afternoon, my mother

00:08:13.480 --> 00:08:15.460
was in the kitchen.

00:08:15.460 --> 00:08:19.510
And I went in to get a
glass of her lemonade.

00:08:19.510 --> 00:08:23.710
And as I was pouring this
lemonade, my mother asked me,

00:08:23.710 --> 00:08:25.660
was I going to
revival that night?

00:08:25.660 --> 00:08:28.330
And I said, yes, ma'am,
for in the South,

00:08:28.330 --> 00:08:30.520
no matter how old you
get, you say, yes, ma'am,

00:08:30.520 --> 00:08:33.490
and no, ma'am, yes, sir, and
no, sir, out of pure respect

00:08:33.490 --> 00:08:35.270
for your elders.

00:08:35.270 --> 00:08:36.940
And so I said, yes,
ma'am, I'm going,

00:08:36.940 --> 00:08:40.240
and I got this glass of
lemonade and went outside.

00:08:40.240 --> 00:08:43.510
About 15 minutes later, I
brought the glass back inside,

00:08:43.510 --> 00:08:48.500
and there my mother was
again in the kitchen.

00:08:48.500 --> 00:08:51.970
She said, what time
revival start tonight?

00:08:51.970 --> 00:08:54.480
And I said 7 o'clock, Mama.

00:08:54.480 --> 00:08:56.480
And she looked at her
watch, and she said, well,

00:08:56.480 --> 00:09:00.254
