there and cut that grass.

00:09:00.254 --> 00:09:03.630
I gave my mother this baby
look, and it usually worked,

00:09:03.630 --> 00:09:06.212
but it didn't work this day.

00:09:06.212 --> 00:09:08.670
And I looked at my mother, and
I said, Mama, I promise you.

00:09:08.670 --> 00:09:12.360
Tomorrow I will cut that grass.

00:09:12.360 --> 00:09:14.080
My mother looked at
me, and she said,

00:09:14.080 --> 00:09:17.560
I'm trying my best
to see how did

00:09:17.560 --> 00:09:23.170
you get you'll cut the grass
tomorrow out of me telling

00:09:23.170 --> 00:09:25.860
you to go cut the grass.

00:09:25.860 --> 00:09:28.320
And she gave me that look
that only she could give me,

00:09:28.320 --> 00:09:31.180
and she finally said, boy,
you better get out there

00:09:31.180 --> 00:09:32.180
and cut grass.

00:09:32.180 --> 00:09:35.190
And I goes outside, and
I fire up the lawn mower.

00:09:35.190 --> 00:09:38.120
And 25 minutes into
cutting the grass,

00:09:38.120 --> 00:09:40.400
I just happened to look up.

00:09:40.400 --> 00:09:42.000
And there stood
two white gentlemen

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:44.450
that I had never seen before.

00:09:44.450 --> 00:09:48.140
I cut the lawn mower off,
and I said, can I help you?

00:09:48.140 --> 00:09:49.760
One of the gentleman
said, yes, we

00:09:49.760 --> 00:09:52.910
are detectives from
Birmingham Police Department.

00:09:52.910 --> 00:09:55.370
We're looking for
Anthony Ray Hinton.

00:09:55.370 --> 00:09:56.420
I said that would be me.

00:09:56.420 --> 00:09:59.270
Again, how can I help you?

00:09:59.270 --> 00:10:02.450
He said, we have a
warrant for your arrest.

00:10:02.450 --> 00:10:04.460
And I said, for what?

00:10:04.460 --> 00:10:06.390
He said, we will explain
that to you later,

00:10:06.390 --> 00:10:09.080
but right now, we want
you to put your hands

00:10:09.080 --> 00:10:11.000
behind your back.

00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:11.720
I complied.

00:10:11.720 --> 00:10:13.280
I put my hands behind my back.

00:10:13.280 --> 00:10:15.530
They put the handcuffs
on me, proceeded

00:10:15.530 --> 00:10:17.990
to put me in the police car.

00:10:17.990 --> 00:10:20.640
And I said, hold up.

00:10:20.640 --> 00:10:24.250
At least allow me
the chance to go in

00:10:24.250 --> 00:10:28.014
and tell my mother that I'm
being arrested for something.

00:10:28.014 --> 00:10:30.430
The detective said, we can't
let you go back in the house,

00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:32.780
and we argued for
about two minutes.

00:10:32.780 --> 00:10:36.010
And finally, the other detective
said, let him go and tell

00:10:36.010 --> 00:10:38.200
his mother he's being arrested.

00:10:38.200 --> 00:10:41.090
And I go in, and I just show
my mother the handcuffs.

00:10:41.090 --> 00:10:46.330
And like any good mother, she
began to scream and holler.

00:10:46.330 --> 00:10:49.380
What are those handcuffs
doing on my baby?

00:10:49.380 --> 00:10:51.330
One of the detectives
said, take him outside

00:10:51.330 --> 00:10:54.700
while I stay in here
and talk to his mother.

00:10:54.700 --> 00:10:56.800
A few minutes later,
he comes outside,

00:10:56.800 --> 00:11:01.120
and we proceeded to
go to the county jail.

00:11:01.120 --> 00:11:04.780
He turned around, and he said,
Anthony, do you own a firearm?

00:11:04.780 --> 00:11:06.340
I said no.

00:11:06.340 --> 00:11:09.070
He said, do your
mother own a firearm?

00:11:09.070 --> 00:11:12.370
I said yes and
told him what kind.

00:11:12.370 --> 00:11:17.290
Every day, any one that meets
me that are aware of this case,

00:11:17.290 --> 00:11:20.490
they ask me one question.

00:11:20.490 --> 00:11:24.330
Why did you tell the
police about a gun

00:11:24.330 --> 00:11:27.100
they had no knowledge of?

00:11:27.100 --> 00:11:31.930
And I tell them that all my
life, my mother have always

00:11:31.930 --> 00:11:34.970
told me, if you
haven't done anything,

00:11:34.970 --> 00:11:37.810
you have no reason to lie.

00:11:37.810 --> 00:11:42.240
If you haven't done anything,
you have no business running.

00:11:42.240 --> 00:11:46.290
That day, I told the truth.

00:11:46.290 --> 00:11:48.120
They dropped me off
at a substation.

00:11:48.120 --> 00:11:50.940
They turned around and go
back to my mother's house

00:11:50.940 --> 00:11:55.110
and talk to her, and
she gives them the gun.

00:11:55.110 --> 00:11:56.050
They kept the gun.

00:11:56.050 --> 00:11:57.670
They come pick me
up, and we proceeded

00:11:57.670 --> 00:12:00.600
to go to the county jail again.

00:12:00.600 --> 00:12:03.630
I asked these detectives
at least 50 times,

00:12:03.630 --> 00:12:05.250
why am I being arrested?

00:12:05.250 --> 00:12:07.380
And they never would respond.

00:12:07.380 --> 00:12:09.890
And after going
[INAUDIBLE],, the detective,

00:12:09.890 --> 00:12:14.220
why are y'all arresting me,
this seemed to set the detective

00:12:14.220 --> 00:12:14.720
off.

00:12:14.720 --> 00:12:15.450
He turned around.

00:12:15.450 --> 00:12:18.330
He looked at me, and
he said, you really

00:12:18.330 --> 00:12:19.990
want to know why
we arresting you?

00:12:19.990 --> 00:12:21.900
I said yes.

00:12:21.900 --> 00:12:23.730
He said, we charging
you with first degree

00:12:23.730 --> 00:12:26.460
robbery, first
degree kidnapping,

00:12:26.460 --> 00:12:29.010
first degree attempted murder.

00:12:29.010 --> 00:12:31.340
I said, oh, you
got the wrong guy.

00:12:31.340 --> 00:12:32.980
He said, let me
tell you something

00:12:32.980 --> 00:12:35.550
and let me tell it
to you right now.

00:12:35.550 --> 00:12:38.670
I don't care whether
you did or didn't do it,

00:12:38.670 --> 00:12:41.780
but I'm going to make sure
you are found guilty of it.

00:12:41.780 --> 00:12:44.880
I said, for a crime
that I didn't commit?

00:12:44.880 --> 00:12:47.550
He said, you must have
a hearing problem,

00:12:47.550 --> 00:12:49.860
because I just told you
I don't care whether you

00:12:49.860 --> 00:12:51.450
did it or didn't do it.

00:12:51.450 --> 00:12:55.950
He said, but you remember this
if you remember nothing else.

00:12:55.950 --> 00:13:01.575
I am going to make sure that
you're found guilty of it.

00:13:01.575 --> 00:13:04.120
We drove a little father,
and he turned around.

00:13:04.120 --> 00:13:06.690
And he said, and
by the way, there's

00:13:06.690 --> 00:13:10.110
five things that are
going to convict you.

00:13:10.110 --> 00:13:11.930
Would you like to
know what they are?

00:13:11.930 --> 00:13:13.740
And I said yes.

00:13:13.740 --> 00:13:16.350
He said, number
one, you're black.

00:13:16.350 --> 00:13:19.260
Number two, a white man is
going to say you shot him.

00:13:19.260 --> 00:13:24.310
Whether you shot him
or not, I don't care.

00:13:24.310 --> 00:13:26.425
He said, number
three, you're going

00:13:26.425 --> 00:13:28.520
to have a white prosecutor.

00:13:28.520 --> 00:13:33.830
Number four, you're going have
a white judge, and number five,

00:13:33.830 --> 00:13:36.700
you're going to have
an all-white jury.

